avoured red and yellow pigments encountered in Nigerian Qur'anic decorations came from coloured minerals, such as ochres-iron oxides red, yellow and sometimes purple brown-which would have been ground and sieved to convert them into pigments.</span>", "label": "Description"}, {"value": "<span>Centre for Research Collections/Main Library</span>", "label": "Location"}, {"value": "<span>Archives</span>", "label": "Subject Category"}, {"value": "<span>Islamic &amp; Asian</span>", "label": "Subject Category"}, {"value": "<span>\u00a9 The University of Edinburgh</span>", "label": "Rights Statement"}, {"value": "<span>Islamic and Asian</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Archives</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Cropped Tiff</span>", "label": "Repro File Type"}, {"value": "<span>88294788</span>", "label": "Repro File Size (bytes)"}, {"value": "<span>Illuminated Prayer Book, Northern Nigeria</span>", "label": "Repro Title"}, {"value": "<span>\u00a9 The University of Edinburgh</span>", "label": "Repro Rights Statement"}, {"value": "<span>2011:09:29 11:28:14</span>", "label": "Repro Capture Date"}]}, {"description": "", "height": 5433, "width": 6899, "@type": "sc:Canvas", "images": [{"on": "https://images.is.ed.ac.uk/luna/servlet/iiif/m/UoEgal~5~5~76726~105870/canvas/c1", "motivation": "sc:painting", "resource": {"service": {"profile": "http://iiif.io/api/image/2/level2.json", "@context": "http://iiif.io/api/image/2/context.json", "@id": "https://images.is.ed.ac.uk/luna/servlet/iiif/UoEgal~5~5~76726~105870"}, "format": "image/jpeg", "height": 5433, "width": 6899, "@id": "https://images.is.ed.ac.uk/luna/servlet/iiif/UoEgal~5~5~76726~105870/full/!1024,1024/0/default.jpg", "@type": "dctypes:Image"}, "@type": "oa:Annotation"}], "label": "Illuminated Prayer Book, Northern Nigeria", "@id": "https://images.is.ed.ac.uk/luna/servlet/iiif/m/UoEgal~5~5~76726~105870/canvas/c1", "thumbnail": {"@id": "https://images.is.ed.ac.uk/MediaManager/srvr?mediafile=/Size0/UoEgal-5-N